webpackJsonp([45676752705715],{1262:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{site:{siteMetadata:{title:"Psyked: James' Web Development website",author:"James Ford"}},markdownRemark:{id:"/Users/James/Repositories/portfolio-2018/src/posts/eslint-visual-studio-code-editor-integration-for-the-win-1bcf38f6ccd4/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<h1>ESLint + Visual Studio Code: Editor integration For The Win</h1>\n<p>Coding is complicated — there are loads of best practices to remember, guidelines to follow and ‘known issues’ to avoid — so it helps to have a ‘helping hand’ while you work.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/1*TPkhIqPgVzFSSpwdlVwhVw-3563cf89bd359ad388df8110da2f08d0-78538.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 398px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 58.542713567839186%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="1 TPkhIqPgVzFSSpwdlVwhVw"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/1*TPkhIqPgVzFSSpwdlVwhVw-3563cf89bd359ad388df8110da2f08d0-78538.png"\n        srcset="/static/1*TPkhIqPgVzFSSpwdlVwhVw-3563cf89bd359ad388df8110da2f08d0-9455c.png 158w,\n/static/1*TPkhIqPgVzFSSpwdlVwhVw-3563cf89bd359ad388df8110da2f08d0-c67e1.png 315w,\n/static/1*TPkhIqPgVzFSSpwdlVwhVw-3563cf89bd359ad388df8110da2f08d0-78538.png 398w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 398px) 100vw, 398px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>ESLint — <a href="https://eslint.org/">https://eslint.org/</a></p>\n<p><a href="https://eslint.org/" title="https://eslint.org/"><strong>ESLint - Pluggable JavaScript linter</strong><br>\n<em>A pluggable and configurable linter tool for identifying and reporting on patterns in JavaScript. Maintain your code…</em>eslint.org</a><a href="https://eslint.org/"></a></p>\n<p><a href="https://eslint.org/">ESLint</a> is an extendible linter — or code checking tool — that can be set up as a standalone tool or integrated into the Visual Studio Code editor.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>‘A linter or lint refers to tools that analyze source code to flag programming errors, bugs, stylistic errors, and suspicious constructs.’ <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lint_%28software%29">[Wikipedia]</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>With ESLint properly configured in your editor, your development experience can be almost as-if you’re continually pair-programming with (an insufferably polite and knowledgeable) know-it-all. And as daunting as that might be, it’ll help you produce better quality code and teach you as you work.</p>\n<hr>\n<h3>Configuring Visual Studio Code with ESLint</h3>\n<p>First, a preamble: I’m going to start by setting up a React project using <code>create-react-app</code>, which gives me a <code>package.json</code> at the root of the project and manages dependencies through NPM.</p>\n<p>To get a new project set up, run the following commands:</p>\n<p><a href="https://github.com/facebook/create-react-app" title="https://github.com/facebook/create-react-app"><strong>facebook/create-react-app</strong><br>\n<em>Create React apps with no build configuration. Contribute to facebook/create-react-app development by creating an…</em>github.com</a><a href="https://github.com/facebook/create-react-app"></a></p>\n<p>First, install <a href="https://github.com/facebook/create-react-app">create-react-app</a>:</p>\n<p>npm i -g create-react-app</p>\n<p>Then, to create a new project:</p>\n<p>create-react-app eslint-integration-example</p>\n<p>And when we want to, we can run the project like so:</p>\n<p>cd eslint-integration-example<br>\nnpm start</p>\n<h4>Setting up ESLint</h4>\n<p>ESLint could be installed globally, but for better portability and resilience let’s add it, and some plugins and settings, to the project, with the following command:</p>\n<p>npm install --save-dev \\<br>\neslint \\<br>\nbabel-eslint \\<br>\neslint-config-airbnb \\<br>\neslint-config-babel \\<br>\neslint-config-prettier \\<br>\neslint-plugin-import \\<br>\neslint-plugin-react</p>\n<p>With all of those plugins installed, my <code>package.json</code> file looks like this:</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/1*xsrntccR6nCD51Gr9zKwvg-c83a04117dffca0c5162e8201047a586-52bc7.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 630px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 131.50470219435738%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="1 xsrntccR6nCD51Gr9zKwvg"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/1*xsrntccR6nCD51Gr9zKwvg-c83a04117dffca0c5162e8201047a586-082ce.png"\n        srcset="/static/1*xsrntccR6nCD51Gr9zKwvg-c83a04117dffca0c5162e8201047a586-c7cb1.png 158w,\n/static/1*xsrntccR6nCD51Gr9zKwvg-c83a04117dffca0c5162e8201047a586-93041.png 315w,\n/static/1*xsrntccR6nCD51Gr9zKwvg-c83a04117dffca0c5162e8201047a586-082ce.png 630w,\n/static/1*xsrntccR6nCD51Gr9zKwvg-c83a04117dffca0c5162e8201047a586-c4006.png 945w,\n/static/1*xsrntccR6nCD51Gr9zKwvg-c83a04117dffca0c5162e8201047a586-85e68.png 1260w,\n/static/1*xsrntccR6nCD51Gr9zKwvg-c83a04117dffca0c5162e8201047a586-52bc7.png 1276w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>The package.json file with ESLint configs and plugins</p>\n<p>Strictly speaking, the necessary plugins for adding ESLint is only actually eslint, but I’ve added the other plugins in this example because they’re the ones I’m currently using in my active projects.</p>\n<p>Alongside these npm packages, we’ll also add a configuration file to the root of the project, called <code>.eslintrc</code>, which looks like this:</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/1*Agug9EAS4QMlUuLOMNyv8Q-40b15374f3f0ff313be006b162c0cb43-15f2a.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 630px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 53.85802469135802%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="1 Agug9EAS4QMlUuLOMNyv8Q"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/1*Agug9EAS4QMlUuLOMNyv8Q-40b15374f3f0ff313be006b162c0cb43-082ce.png"\n        srcset="/static/1*Agug9EAS4QMlUuLOMNyv8Q-40b15374f3f0ff313be006b162c0cb43-c7cb1.png 158w,\n/static/1*Agug9EAS4QMlUuLOMNyv8Q-40b15374f3f0ff313be006b162c0cb43-93041.png 315w,\n/static/1*Agug9EAS4QMlUuLOMNyv8Q-40b15374f3f0ff313be006b162c0cb43-082ce.png 630w,\n/static/1*Agug9EAS4QMlUuLOMNyv8Q-40b15374f3f0ff313be006b162c0cb43-c4006.png 945w,\n/static/1*Agug9EAS4QMlUuLOMNyv8Q-40b15374f3f0ff313be006b162c0cb43-85e68.png 1260w,\n/static/1*Agug9EAS4QMlUuLOMNyv8Q-40b15374f3f0ff313be006b162c0cb43-15f2a.png 1296w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>My .eslintrc file</p>\n<p>This tells ESLint to import the <strong>airbnb</strong>, <strong>prettier</strong> and <strong>jsx-a11y</strong> configurations (that we installed in the previous command) as a starting point, and gives us a springboard from which to extend the configuration in the future.</p>\n<p>To run eslint against our code we can use the following command:</p>\n<p>npx eslint src/App.js</p>\n<p>Which gives the following output in the terminal:</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/1*_P4YPpbVg4L-Utu7egF-vg-db2b0acbbbb197f15abf6fb5c9adbb51-c17a6.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 630px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 32.43243243243243%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="1  P4YPpbVg4L Utu7egF vg"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/1*_P4YPpbVg4L-Utu7egF-vg-db2b0acbbbb197f15abf6fb5c9adbb51-082ce.png"\n        srcset="/static/1*_P4YPpbVg4L-Utu7egF-vg-db2b0acbbbb197f15abf6fb5c9adbb51-c7cb1.png 158w,\n/static/1*_P4YPpbVg4L-Utu7egF-vg-db2b0acbbbb197f15abf6fb5c9adbb51-93041.png 315w,\n/static/1*_P4YPpbVg4L-Utu7egF-vg-db2b0acbbbb197f15abf6fb5c9adbb51-082ce.png 630w,\n/static/1*_P4YPpbVg4L-Utu7egF-vg-db2b0acbbbb197f15abf6fb5c9adbb51-c4006.png 945w,\n/static/1*_P4YPpbVg4L-Utu7egF-vg-db2b0acbbbb197f15abf6fb5c9adbb51-85e68.png 1260w,\n/static/1*_P4YPpbVg4L-Utu7egF-vg-db2b0acbbbb197f15abf6fb5c9adbb51-c17a6.png 1480w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Test output from the terminal</p>\n<p>To make things a little easier to run, we can also add this command to the scripts section of the <code>package.json</code> file, making it look like this:</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/1*WIn_eNNTYewBEd9AAuO8-g-335ee1d264605dc90957bfd45ffb47cf-14659.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 630px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 59.74025974025974%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="1 WIn eNNTYewBEd9AAuO8 g"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/1*WIn_eNNTYewBEd9AAuO8-g-335ee1d264605dc90957bfd45ffb47cf-082ce.png"\n        srcset="/static/1*WIn_eNNTYewBEd9AAuO8-g-335ee1d264605dc90957bfd45ffb47cf-c7cb1.png 158w,\n/static/1*WIn_eNNTYewBEd9AAuO8-g-335ee1d264605dc90957bfd45ffb47cf-93041.png 315w,\n/static/1*WIn_eNNTYewBEd9AAuO8-g-335ee1d264605dc90957bfd45ffb47cf-082ce.png 630w,\n/static/1*WIn_eNNTYewBEd9AAuO8-g-335ee1d264605dc90957bfd45ffb47cf-14659.png 770w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>The scripts section of the package.json file</p>\n<p>It’s already pretty neat to be able to run ESLint and highlight issues with our code like this, but what really takes it to the next level is editor integration.</p>\n<h4>Integrating with Visual Studio Code</h4>\n<p>The ESLint plugin can be installed from the Visual Studio Marketplace, and gives easy integration with Visual Studio Code.</p>\n<p><a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=dbaeumer.vscode-eslint" title="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=dbaeumer.vscode-eslint"><strong>ESLint - Visual Studio Marketplace</strong><br>\n<em>Extension for Visual Studio Code - Integrates ESLint JavaScript into VS Code.</em>marketplace.visualstudio.com</a><a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=dbaeumer.vscode-eslint"></a></p>\n<p>What does it actually do though? It adds inline code error highlighting, which transforms your editing experience (as illustrated below)</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/1*O6Q5VDIKC4UM_sfJOlE82w-5da123ec4eb2ad085f170b0781303f08-56bef.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 630px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 62.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="1 O6Q5VDIKC4UM sfJOlE82w"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/1*O6Q5VDIKC4UM_sfJOlE82w-5da123ec4eb2ad085f170b0781303f08-082ce.png"\n        srcset="/static/1*O6Q5VDIKC4UM_sfJOlE82w-5da123ec4eb2ad085f170b0781303f08-c7cb1.png 158w,\n/static/1*O6Q5VDIKC4UM_sfJOlE82w-5da123ec4eb2ad085f170b0781303f08-93041.png 315w,\n/static/1*O6Q5VDIKC4UM_sfJOlE82w-5da123ec4eb2ad085f170b0781303f08-082ce.png 630w,\n/static/1*O6Q5VDIKC4UM_sfJOlE82w-5da123ec4eb2ad085f170b0781303f08-c4006.png 945w,\n/static/1*O6Q5VDIKC4UM_sfJOlE82w-5da123ec4eb2ad085f170b0781303f08-56bef.png 1200w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/1*n20krHQQGci7D347-4HELQ-e3b8ec3f92cd8aeb8b5a95af32d2643e-56bef.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 630px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 62.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="1 n20krHQQGci7D347 4HELQ"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/1*n20krHQQGci7D347-4HELQ-e3b8ec3f92cd8aeb8b5a95af32d2643e-082ce.png"\n        srcset="/static/1*n20krHQQGci7D347-4HELQ-e3b8ec3f92cd8aeb8b5a95af32d2643e-c7cb1.png 158w,\n/static/1*n20krHQQGci7D347-4HELQ-e3b8ec3f92cd8aeb8b5a95af32d2643e-93041.png 315w,\n/static/1*n20krHQQGci7D347-4HELQ-e3b8ec3f92cd8aeb8b5a95af32d2643e-082ce.png 630w,\n/static/1*n20krHQQGci7D347-4HELQ-e3b8ec3f92cd8aeb8b5a95af32d2643e-c4006.png 945w,\n/static/1*n20krHQQGci7D347-4HELQ-e3b8ec3f92cd8aeb8b5a95af32d2643e-56bef.png 1200w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>On the left: Without ESLint integration, On the right: With ESLint integration</p>\n<p>With the plugin set up, rather than having the ESLint as a task that needs to be invoked manually, it runs automatically, displays the results inline with your code, and updates as you type so you get the kind of user experience you’d expect from a spell-checker but with the complexity of your ESLint rules.</p>\n<p>It’s not all about inline validation though, there’s also some sweet integration with the rest of the editor, such as the ‘Problems’ panel:</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/1*dvvNjcPydPLfeOswJ9u-Sg-83f36beb4fae8700dc8cc85c93d0c31e-85ae7.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 630px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 62.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="1 dvvNjcPydPLfeOswJ9u Sg"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/1*dvvNjcPydPLfeOswJ9u-Sg-83f36beb4fae8700dc8cc85c93d0c31e-082ce.png"\n        srcset="/static/1*dvvNjcPydPLfeOswJ9u-Sg-83f36beb4fae8700dc8cc85c93d0c31e-c7cb1.png 158w,\n/static/1*dvvNjcPydPLfeOswJ9u-Sg-83f36beb4fae8700dc8cc85c93d0c31e-93041.png 315w,\n/static/1*dvvNjcPydPLfeOswJ9u-Sg-83f36beb4fae8700dc8cc85c93d0c31e-082ce.png 630w,\n/static/1*dvvNjcPydPLfeOswJ9u-Sg-83f36beb4fae8700dc8cc85c93d0c31e-c4006.png 945w,\n/static/1*dvvNjcPydPLfeOswJ9u-Sg-83f36beb4fae8700dc8cc85c93d0c31e-85e68.png 1260w,\n/static/1*dvvNjcPydPLfeOswJ9u-Sg-83f36beb4fae8700dc8cc85c93d0c31e-85ae7.png 1600w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>(above) ESLint integration with the ‘Problems’ panel</p>\n<h4>Extension Suggestions</h4>\n<p>Seeing this editor integration does rely on having the correct plugin installed though, which can be a bit of a tedious task to maintain if you’re on a development team. To assist with this, we can add a VSCode extensions configuration file, which will prompt Visual Studio Code to suggest the installation of extensions when appropriate.</p>\n<p>Create a file called <code>extensions.json</code> in a directory named <code>.vscode</code> in the root of the project, with the following content:</p>\n<p>{<br>\n"recommendations": [<br>\n"dbaeumer.vscode-eslint",<br>\n"esbenp.prettier-vscode",<br>\n"dzannotti.vscode-babel-coloring"<br>\n]<br>\n}</p>\n<p>The official documentation for this feature can be found here:</p>\n<p><a href="https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/editor/extension-gallery#_workspace-recommended-extensions" title="https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/editor/extension-gallery#_workspace-recommended-extensions"><strong>Managing Extensions in Visual Studio Code</strong><br>\n<em>The features that Visual Studio Code includes out-of-the-box are just the start. VS Code extensions let you add…</em>code.visualstudio.com</a><a href="https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/editor/extension-gallery#_workspace-recommended-extensions"></a></p>\n<hr>\n<h4>Why ESLint?</h4>\n<p>What makes ESLint cool is that it’s something that can be extended to check for more than just logical code errors, it can check for things like accessibility issues or inconsistent code formatting, which is why I’ve added <a href="https://github.com/evcohen/eslint-plugin-jsx-a11y">react-jsx-a11y</a> and the <a href="https://github.com/prettier/prettier-eslint">prettier</a> plugins to plugins list.</p>\n<p>And with all of that setup, you can experience what it’s like to Pair Program with a stickler for consistency and best practices, without actually having to be pairing.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/1*84wQvgcY-qeS92WYYvJBTA-8e5595acb8450ef824b9fd2abb42cd3e-3a143.jpeg"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 630px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/jpeg;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="1 84wQvgcY qeS92WYYvJBTA"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/1*84wQvgcY-qeS92WYYvJBTA-8e5595acb8450ef824b9fd2abb42cd3e-af57e.jpeg"\n        srcset="/static/1*84wQvgcY-qeS92WYYvJBTA-8e5595acb8450ef824b9fd2abb42cd3e-847f7.jpeg 158w,\n/static/1*84wQvgcY-qeS92WYYvJBTA-8e5595acb8450ef824b9fd2abb42cd3e-93973.jpeg 315w,\n/static/1*84wQvgcY-qeS92WYYvJBTA-8e5595acb8450ef824b9fd2abb42cd3e-af57e.jpeg 630w,\n/static/1*84wQvgcY-qeS92WYYvJBTA-8e5595acb8450ef824b9fd2abb42cd3e-28cf9.jpeg 945w,\n/static/1*84wQvgcY-qeS92WYYvJBTA-8e5595acb8450ef824b9fd2abb42cd3e-0d474.jpeg 1260w,\n/static/1*84wQvgcY-qeS92WYYvJBTA-8e5595acb8450ef824b9fd2abb42cd3e-3a143.jpeg 1600w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Photo by <a href="https://unsplash.com/photos/ZKBzlifgkgw?utm_source=unsplash&#x26;utm_medium=referral&#x26;utm_content=creditCopyText">Mimi Thian</a> on <a href="https://unsplash.com/search/photos/pointing-at-code?utm_source=unsplash&#x26;utm_medium=referral&#x26;utm_content=creditCopyText">Unsplash</a></p>',frontmatter:{title:"ESLint + Visual Studio Code: Editor integration For The Win",date:"October 18, 2018",tags:["JavaScript","Eslint","Visual Studio Code","Developer Tools","Tech"],url:"https://medium.com/comparethemarket/eslint-visual-studio-code-editor-integration-for-the-win-1bcf38f6ccd4",image:null,description:"Coding is complicated so  it helps to have a ‘helping hand’ while you work."}}},pathContext:{prev:{frontmatter:{path:"/blog/colours-a-lightning-talk/",tags:["Front End Development","Side Project","Presentations","Colour","Tech"],title:"Colours: A lightning Talk ⚡️",date:"2018-09-24T12:32:50.599Z",description:"I find colours fascinating, and I write code that goes into websites, so there’s bound to be a natural intersection between those two…",image:null}},next:{frontmatter:{path:"/blog/putting-our-component-library-on-a-diet-88aee7f457a/",tags:["JavaScript","Rollup","Webpack","Front End Development","Tech"],title:"Putting our Component library on a diet.",date:"2018-11-06T16:49:11.453Z",description:"Performance matters, and “Houston, we have a problem.”",image:null}}}}}});
